{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id62d90c06-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t25/s5118"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"5118"},"text":"§ 5118.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Application generally","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The provisions of this Act shall not apply to any of the Territories, colonies, or insular possessions of the United States, except that sections 9, 10, 11, 12, and 16 [","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t25/s5112"},"text":"25 U.S.C. 5112","children":[],"tail":", 5113, 5115, 5116, 5123] shall apply to the Territory of Alaska: "},{"tag":"i","attrib":{},"text":"Provided","children":[],"tail":", That sections 4, 7, 16, 17, and 18 of this Act ["},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t25/s5107"},"text":"25 U.S.C. 5107","children":[],"tail":", 5110, 5123, 5124, 5125] shall not apply to the following-named Indian tribes, the members of such Indian tribes, together with members of other tribes affiliated with such named tribes located in the State of Oklahoma, as follows: Cheyenne, Arapaho, Apache, Comanche, Kiowa, Caddo, Delaware, Wichita, Osage, Kaw, Otoe, Tonkawa, Pawnee, Ponca, Shawnee, Ottawa, Quapaw, Seneca, Wyandotte, Iowa, Sac and Fox, Kickapoo, Pottawatomi, Cherokee, Chickasaw, Choctaw, Creek, and Seminole. Section 4 of this Act ["},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t25/s5107"},"text":"25 U.S.C. 5107","children":[],"tail":"] shall not apply to the Indians of the Klamath Reservation in Oregon."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id62db55f7-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1934-06-18/ch576/s13"},"text":"June 18, 1934, ch. 576, § 13","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/48/986"},"text":"48 Stat. 986","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/301/s3/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–301, § 3(b)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1990-05-24"},"text":"May 24, 1990","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/104/207"},"text":"104 Stat. 207","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id62db55f8-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id62db55f9-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"id62db55fa-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"This Act, referred to in text, is ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1934-06-18/ch576"},"text":"act June 18, 1934, ch. 576","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/48/984"},"text":"48 Stat. 984","children":[],"tail":", popularly known as the Indian Reorganization Act, which is classified generally to this chapter. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see Short Title note set out under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t25/s5101"},"text":"section 5101 of this title","children":[],"tail":" and Tables."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"codification","id":"id62db55fb-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Codification","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section was formerly classified to ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t25/s473"},"text":"section 473 of this title","children":[],"tail":" prior to editorial reclassification and renumbering as this section."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"id62db55fc-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1990—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/301"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–301","children":[],"tail":" substituted “sections 4,” for “sections 2, 4,” in proviso."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"execDoc","id":"id62db55fd-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Executive Documents","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneous","id":"id62db55fe-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Admission of Alaska as State","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Admission of Alaska into the Union was accomplished ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1959-01-03"},"text":"Jan. 3, 1959","children":[],"tail":", on issuance of Proc. No. 3269, "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1959-01-03"},"text":"Jan. 3, 1959","children":[],"tail":", 24 F.R. 81, 73 Stat. c16, as required by sections 1 and 8(c) of "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/85/508"},"text":"Pub. L. 85–508","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1958-07-07"},"text":"July 7, 1958","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/72/339"},"text":"72 Stat. 339","children":[],"tail":", set out as notes preceding "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t48/s21"},"text":"section 21 of Title 48","children":[],"tail":", Territories and Insular Possessions."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
